							</div>	
							<div class="entry-content"> <p>This is a GPU miner I built to mine Dogecoin several months ago. The main components are the GPU&#8217;s, and this rig ended up containing 4 R9 290&#8242;s.</p>
<p>Max hash rate was around 3.4KH/s, but unfortunately this rig was stolen! I had it running in the X-Labs hackerspace room at USF and someone stole it in the middle of the night (door was accidentally left unlocked). This has been a big setback for me as this rig cost upwards of 2.5k to build along with many hours of my time.</p>
<p>I&#8217;m slowly constructing another mining rig and general purpose server out of older parts sourced from Craigslist. That rig is almost complete, but won&#8217;t be able to mine nearly as much as my first rig.</p>
<p>Hopefully I&#8217;ll be able to write some tutorials or an ebook for setting up mining rigs of this sort soon.</p>
